  "text": "To solve the issue, the first fully reconfigurable CMOS-NVM processor includes an scaling stage in the form of percolumn current dividers, interfacing the ADCs before the conversion takes place [CITATION_1] . While maintaining reconfigurability, the system is penalized in terms of area and power consumption. Additionally, the system includes high-precision DACs/ADCs, incurring in notizeable area and power penalties.",
